# No Automatic Git Commits

The user controls all git commits manually. Angelo must not trigger or perform
automatic git commits in this repo.

## Rules

1. **Never run `git commit` or `git push` unless the user explicitly asks.**
2. **Never run `angelo memory commit` or `angelo zettelkasten commit`.**
3. **When calling memory `record()`, do not pass the `files` parameter** unless
   the user explicitly asks to git-pin an entry to specific files. Omitting
   `files` prevents Angelo's file-pinning logic from auto-committing source code.
4. **Memory and zettelkasten writes are fine** — they create/update files under
   `.memory/` and `.zettelkasten/` on disk. Those directories are gitignored so
   Angelo's debounced committers will not commit them.
5. **When the user asks to commit**, stage and commit only what they specify.
   Do not bundle Angelo memory/zettelkasten files unless they ask.

## Note

If `.memory/` or `.zettelkasten/` files are ever manually tracked with
`git add -f`, Angelo may resume auto-committing those tracked paths. Keep them
untracked and rely on manual `git add -f` when committing.
